{
  "texts": [
    "Instead, they only need to avoid the known years.",
    "In addition, due to the sparsity of the overall annotated variants in the Pub-Med abstracts, the sentences containing the entity type of variant in the abstracts spanning the years from 1980 to 2019 but not in our 400 annotated articles were also collected as part of the BERN-annotated PubMed corpus to increase the number of variants.",
    "Data PreprocessingBoth 549,587 BERN-annotated abstracts and our annotated 400 articles were divided into train/validation/test datasets at the ratio of 7:2:1 randomly for model training, validating and testing for Phase I and Phase II model of BERT, respectively.",
    "All the corpora were converted into CoNLL format and labeled using BIO format [46].",
    "ModelIn order to build NER predictive models for both offline inference and online inference, a large model and a compact model were designed correspondingly, namely, BERT-based NER and DistilBERT-based NER, as is shown in Fig. 2a."
  ]
}